%pyspark

from pyspark.sql import HiveContext
sqlContext = HiveContext(sc)

%pyspark

sqlContext.sql("""CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE bikepoint.history_ext
(id STRING,
bikes INT,
docks INT,
lat FLOAT,
lon FLOAT,
polled_time STRING,
spaces INT,
update_time STRING)
ROW FORMAT DELIMITED FIELDS TERMINATED BY ','
LOCATION '/user/slbm/bikepoint-history/'""")

%sql
SELECT *
FROM bikepoint.history_ext
WHERE id in ('BikePoints_195')

%pyspark

sqlContext.sql("""CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE bikepoint.bikepoints
(id STRING,
borough STRING,
chx_dist FLOAT, 
easting FLOAT,
inner_london INT,
lat FLOAT,
lon FLOAT,
northing FLOAT)
ROW FORMAT DELIMITED FIELDS TERMINATED BY ','
LOCATION '/user/slbm/bikepoint-ref/'""")

%sql
SELECT id,
AVG(spaces),
MAX(chx_dist)
FROM bikepoint.historyjoined
WHERE polled_time_ampk = 1
GROUP BY id
